election_record.label: Massachusetts 1792 Electoral College, Western District

overview.note: A majority of votes was required to be elected. As no electors received a majority of votes, the Massachusetts General Court selected the five electors. William Shepard, Moses Gill, Dwight Foster, Thompson J. Skinner and Ebenezer Mattoon, Jr. were selected.

There were no affiliations or elector declarations in the Original Election Returns. William Shepard, Moses Gill, Dwight Foster, Thompson J. Skinner and Ebenezer Mattoon, Jr. voted for George Washington and John Adams in the Electoral College.
